//Weapon (battleaxe), artifact (requires attunement)//

The blade of Noctra is a formless blade of dark magic, that can be attached to an object to fill it with immense power of the arcane Goddess of shadows. The power of the blade is drawn directly from the wielder, meaning it can only be effective in the hands of the most worthy.

**Magic Weapon.** The //Blade of the Shadow Queen// is a magic weapon that grants a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with it. If wielded by a being of level 5 or higher, the blade also functions as a [http://sxlaris.wikidot.com/5e:gauntlet-of-darkness Guantlet of Darkness]. At level 10, it also functions as a [http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/wondrous-items:dwarven-thrower Dwarven Thrower], and at level 15, it functions as a [http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/wondrous-items:sword-of-sharpness Sword of Sharpness]. The attack/accuracy bonus improves by +1 with each of these levels as well, making it a +3 weapon at level 15. This is tied to overall character level, not class level.

**Random Properties.** The blade has the following randomly determined properties:

* While attuned to the artifact, you can use an action to cast [https://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:glyph-of-warding Glyph of Warding] from it. After you cast the spell, roll a d6. On a roll of 1-3, you can't cast it again until after a long rest.
* While attuned to the artifact, you can't be charmed or frightened.

* While attuned to the artifact, you regain 1d4 hit points at the start of your turn if you have at least 1 hit point.

* While attuned to the artifact, you are blinded when you are more than 20 feet away from it.
* While attuned to the artifact, you are deafened when you are more than 20 feet away from it.

**Blessings of Noctra.** If you are a Child of Noctra attuned to the blade, you gain the following benefits:

* You have immunity to poison damage.
* The range of your darkvision increases by 5 feet for every level starting at level 5.[[footnote]]You should end with 75 additional feet of darkvision at level 20.[[/footnote]]
* You gain proficiency with artisan's tools related to alchemy, brewing, and jewling.
* At level 19, you have immunity to necrotic damage.

**Conjure Shadow Elemental.** If you are holding the axe, you can use your action to cast the [http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:conjure-elemental Conjure Elemental] spell from it, summoning a specialized shadow elemental. The elemental has the stats of an Earth Elemental, but replaces Earthglide, with Shadowglide. You can't use this property again until the next dawn.

**Travel the Depths.** You can use an action to touch the axe to a fixed piece of dwarven stonework and cast the teleport spell from the axe. If your intended destination is underground, there is no chance of a mishap or arriving somewhere unexpected. You can't use this property again until 3 days have passed.

**Curse.** The axe bears a curse that affects any nondrow that becomes attuned to it. Even if the attunement ends, the curse remains. With each passing day, the creature's physical appearance and stature become more drowlike. After seven days, the creature looks like a typical drow, but the creature neither loses its racial traits nor gains the racial traits of a drow. The physical changes wrought by the axe aren't considered magical in nature (and therefore can't be dispelled), but they can be undone by any effect that removes a curse, such as a [http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:greater-restoration Greater Restoration] or [http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:remove-curse Remove Curse] spell.

